defaultXenia Dormandydefault is the Project Director of the US 
defaultProgramme
default and the Acting Dean of the Academy for Leadership in International Affairs at Chatham House.  From 2009-2011, she was the Executive Director of the 
defaultPeaceNexus
default Foundation in Switzerland.  Prior to this, Xenia was Executive Director of Harvard Kennedy School’s 
defaultBelfer
default Center for Science and International Affairs, Director of the Project on India and the Subcontinent, and a member of the Board of the 
defaultBelfer
default Center.  From 2001-05, Xenia worked at the US State Department on issues from nonproliferation, to homeland security and South Asia.  She also spent six months helping to set up the Homeland Security Office in the Office of the Vice President, and was Director for South Asia at the US National Security Council. 
